  "body": "crowdfund example fails sometimes, e.g. ![Screenshot from 2022-04-05 21-56-53](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3867501/161880485-b6abe209-d4fd-4eae-951b-c883b1c5a223.png)\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/runs/5842719555?check_suite_focus=true\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nSeems like a spurious failure -- the first block is taking longer than one second to mine, causing `c.block_timestamp()` be offset by more than one from the contract creation block.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n2 options: 1) measure the time the first block takes to mine, and then check that `c.deadline() - c.block_timestamp() == <elapsed_time>`, or 2) query the blockchain for the difference between the two timestamps?",
